# ERP optimization checklist

Apply on **every** change. Goal: structured, DRY, type-safe code with zero `tsc` errors.

## Before marking done

1. `pnpm exec tsc --noEmit` — fix all type errors
2. No duplicated defaults — import from a single source (`DEFAULT_DOCUMENT_TEMPLATE_SETTINGS`, `documentTotal`, etc.)
3. No duplicated validation — reuse helpers (`parseDocumentScopeQuery`, `assertCompanyAccess`, `normalizeLines`)
4. Match the nearest completed module (Sales → Procurement → Inventory)

## Structure (do not skip layers)

```
page.tsx → lib/data → api/route → lib/server → migration
```

- Business logic in `lib/server/` — never in `page.tsx` or route beyond auth + dispatch
- Shared columns/headers in `components/modules/*-shared.tsx`
- Cross-module logic in dedicated libs (`lib/documents/`, `lib/org/`, `lib/server/document-scope.ts`)

## React & client performance

- **Zustand object selectors**: use `useShallow` from `zustand/react/shallow` to avoid re-renders
- **Document scope**: `useDocumentContext()` — one hook, store-backed (see `erp-document-context.mdc`)
- **Parallel fetches**: `Promise.all([fetchA(), fetchB()])` in page `load` callbacks
- **Effects**: cancel async work on unmount (`let cancelled = false` pattern in `use-print-context.ts`)
- **Memo**: `useCallback` for `load` functions with correct deps; avoid inline object/array deps in hot paths

## Server & data

- **Org lookups**: index with `Map` when resolving company/branch/warehouse in loops (`document-context.ts` pattern)
- **Supabase lists**: `.match(documentScopeFilter(...))` + narrow `.select()` — no `select('*')` when joins suffice
- **Mappers**: pure `mapX(row)` functions; coerce types once in server layer
- **Parallel DB reads**: `Promise.all` for independent queries (see `getDocumentTemplateSettings`)

## Migrations

- Idempotent: `IF NOT EXISTS`, `DROP TRIGGER IF EXISTS`, `do $$ … exception when duplicate_object`
- Prefer **enum types** over text + check constraints for fixed value sets
- Section headers (`-- ---`) and `comment on` for non-obvious columns
- One concern per file; log in `PROGRESS_INDEX.md` §8

## Anti-patterns (reject in review)

| Bad | Good |
|-----|------|
| New feature with no `feat_*` flag | Flag in Feature Management + `isFeatureEnabled` |
| Copy-paste default template fields | `DEFAULT_DOCUMENT_TEMPLATE_SETTINGS` |
| `currentCompanyId` for document API calls | `useDocumentContext()` |
| Inline `companyId required` in every route | `parseDocumentScopeQuery()` |
| God file >500 lines | Split by concern |
| Mock-only page when DB path exists | Wire API or mark coming-soon |
| Calculation logic in page/dialog | `lib/sales/calculations.ts` or `lib/documents/` |

## Docs sync

After user-facing changes: update `PROGRESS_INDEX.md` per `erp-docs-and-features.mdc`.

